ch.epfl.alpano.gui

Class PanoramaUserParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.epfl.alpano.gui.PanoramaUserParameters

  • public final class PanoramaUserParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows for the creation of Panorama parameters but insures that the given arguments are contained within the model of our terrain. If illegal arguments are given they will be sanitized which means that they will be brought within the domain of our model.

    This class should be used for safe creation of PanoramaParameters. The advantage of using this class instead of PanoramaParameters is that this class insures that the given arguments are going to be within the DEM that we have available for computing the terrain.

    Author:
    Martin Cibils (261746), Jeremy Mion (261178)

      • panoramaParameters

        public PanoramaParameters panoramaParameters()
        Creates a PanoramaParameter that needs to be computed. This PanoramaPArameter takes into account the supper sampling.

        Supper sampling is a method to allow for a nicer image to be calculated. The edges in the image will be smother. The super sampling exponent will be used to scale the calculated image.

        Let:

        wi = the width of the displayed image.

        hi = the height of the displayed image.

        wp = the width of the calculated image.

        hp = the height of the calculated image.

        s = the supper sampling value.

        wp = 2s * wi

        hp = 2s * hi

        Returns:
        The parameters of the panorama that need to be computed. Includes the supper sampling.
        See Also:
        PanoramaParameters
